<section id="primary" class="pt-sm-5 taxonomy_section">
<main id="main" class="site-main" role="main">
<div class="container pt-sm-4 px-sm-5 py-3 single_page_frame">
<div class=" mb-5 mt-4" style="border-bottom:1px #543176 dotted">
<h3 class="text-normal text-vdbgray mb-3 mt-5">Myanmar keyword: <span>Union Tax Law ("UTL")</span> </h3>
<div class="pl-md-4">
<div class="font-weight-bold"><a class="text-vdbpurple" href="https://www.vdb-loi.com/mm_publications/amended-union-tax-law-2021-increases-the-commercial-tax-rate-on-internet-services-and-expands-the-income-range-of-undisclosed-source-of-income/">Amended Union Tax Law 2021 increases the commercial tax rate on internet services and expands the income range of undisclosed source of income</a></div>
<div class="text-vdbgray small">February 14, 2022</div>
<div><a class="font-italic text-vdbaqua small" href="https://www.vdb-loi.com/mm_publications/amended-union-tax-law-2021-increases-the-commercial-tax-rate-on-internet-services-and-expands-the-income-range-of-undisclosed-source-of-income/">https://www.vdb-loi.com/mm_publications/amended-union-tax-law-2021-increases-the-commercial-tax-rate-on-internet-services-and-expands-the-income-range-of-undisclosed-source-of-income/</a></div>
<div class="font-italic"><p>The State Administration Council enacted Law No. 1/2022 on Amending the Union Tax Law 2021 (“Amended UTL 2021”) on 6 January 2022 to increase the commercial tax rate over internet services and expand the income layers of undisclosed sources of income for the financial year 2021-2022. The Amended UTL 2021 took effect on 8 January [&hellip;]</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="pl-md-4">
<div class="font-weight-bold"><a class="text-vdbpurple" href="https://www.vdb-loi.com/mm_publications/what-major-changes-are-included-under-the-union-tax-law-2021/">What Major Changes Are Included Under The Union Tax Law 2021?</a></div>
<div class="text-vdbgray small">January 21, 2022</div>
<div><a class="font-italic text-vdbaqua small" href="https://www.vdb-loi.com/mm_publications/what-major-changes-are-included-under-the-union-tax-law-2021/">https://www.vdb-loi.com/mm_publications/what-major-changes-are-included-under-the-union-tax-law-2021/</a></div>
<div class="font-italic"><p>The Union Tax Law 2021 (“UTL 2021”) was enacted on 30 September 2021 by the State Administration Council (“SAC”). It is applicable for the financial year (“FY”) 2021-2022 (1 October 2021 to 31 March 2022). Some notable changes under the UTL 2021 for taxpayers are the reductions in tax rates on the taxable profits of [&hellip;]</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="pl-md-4">
<div class="font-weight-bold"><a class="text-vdbpurple" href="https://www.vdb-loi.com/mm_publications/reduced-personal-income-tax-under-utl-2021/">Reduced Personal Income Tax under UTL 2021</a></div>
<div class="text-vdbgray small">January 20, 2022</div>
<div><a class="font-italic text-vdbaqua small" href="https://www.vdb-loi.com/mm_publications/reduced-personal-income-tax-under-utl-2021/">https://www.vdb-loi.com/mm_publications/reduced-personal-income-tax-under-utl-2021/</a></div>
<div class="font-italic"><p>In order to shore up the economy and investments affected by the COVID-19 pandemic; the state administration council has increased the income ranges at each rate level applicable for Personal Income Tax (“PIT”) in Union Tax Law (“UTL”) 2021 dated 30 September 2021. The changes under UTL 2021 are more favorable for taxpayers, since more [&hellip;]</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="pl-md-4">
<div class="font-weight-bold"><a class="text-vdbpurple" href="https://www.vdb-loi.com/mm_publications/continued-tax-amnesty-on-undisclosed-income-at-slightly-higher-income-tax-rates/">Continued Tax Amnesty on Undisclosed Income at Slightly Higher Income Tax Rates</a></div>
<div class="text-vdbgray small">August 31, 2020</div>
<div><a class="font-italic text-vdbaqua small" href="https://www.vdb-loi.com/mm_publications/continued-tax-amnesty-on-undisclosed-income-at-slightly-higher-income-tax-rates/">https://www.vdb-loi.com/mm_publications/continued-tax-amnesty-on-undisclosed-income-at-slightly-higher-income-tax-rates/</a></div>
<div class="font-italic"><p>If an individual or a company is buying a capital asset or making an investment, the source of income is required to be provided as proof for the funds used for the purchase or the investment. If the source of income cannot be proved for the portion of the funds used in such purchase or [&hellip;]</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="pl-md-4">
<div class="font-weight-bold"><a class="text-vdbpurple" href="https://www.vdb-loi.com/mm_publications/the-draft-union-tax-law-2020-and-key-takeaways-from-recent-changes-in-tax-regulations/">The Draft Union Tax Law 2020 and Key Takeaways From Recent Changes in Tax Regulations</a></div>
<div class="text-vdbgray small">July 30, 2020</div>
<div><a class="font-italic text-vdbaqua small" href="https://www.vdb-loi.com/mm_publications/the-draft-union-tax-law-2020-and-key-takeaways-from-recent-changes-in-tax-regulations/">https://www.vdb-loi.com/mm_publications/the-draft-union-tax-law-2020-and-key-takeaways-from-recent-changes-in-tax-regulations/</a></div>
<div class="font-italic"><p>The past few months have been an interesting phase for taxpayers in Myanmar due to the tax reliefs granted under the COVID-19 Economic Relief Plan, changes in current tax regulations, the announcement of the draft Union Tax Law 2020 (“draft UTL”), and the draft new Income Tax Law.&nbsp;&nbsp; What major changes are included under the [&hellip;]</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="pl-md-4">
<div class="font-weight-bold"><a class="text-vdbpurple" href="https://www.vdb-loi.com/mm_publications/union-tax-law-2019-everything-you-need-to-know-about-amnesty-exemptions-and-significant-changes/">Union Tax Law 2019: Everything you need to know about amnesty, exemptions and significant changes</a></div>
<div class="text-vdbgray small">September 30, 2019</div>
<div><a class="font-italic text-vdbaqua small" href="https://www.vdb-loi.com/mm_publications/union-tax-law-2019-everything-you-need-to-know-about-amnesty-exemptions-and-significant-changes/">https://www.vdb-loi.com/mm_publications/union-tax-law-2019-everything-you-need-to-know-about-amnesty-exemptions-and-significant-changes/</a></div>
<div class="font-italic"><p>The Union Taw Law (“UTL”) 2019 was enacted on 24 September 2019 by the Union Parliament (the Pyidaungsu Hluttaw) and will be applicable for the Financial Year (“FY”) 2019-2020 (1 October 2019 to 30 September 2020). With the new income year commencing on 1 October 2019 and the Tax Administration Law (“TAL”) coming into force, [&hellip;]</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="pl-md-4">
<div class="font-weight-bold"><a class="text-vdbpurple" href="https://www.vdb-loi.com/mm_publications/second-chance-to-re-register-your-company-before-being-struck-off-the-registry/">Second chance to re-register your company before being struck off the registry</a></div>
<div class="text-vdbgray small">March 22, 2019</div>
<div><a class="font-italic text-vdbaqua small" href="https://www.vdb-loi.com/mm_publications/second-chance-to-re-register-your-company-before-being-struck-off-the-registry/">https://www.vdb-loi.com/mm_publications/second-chance-to-re-register-your-company-before-being-struck-off-the-registry/</a></div>
<div class="font-italic"><p>According to the recent Directorate of Investment and Company Administration (“DICA”) announcement issued on 8th&nbsp;March 2019, companies who missed the 31 January deadline now have until&nbsp;March 30&nbsp;to re-register. However, any companies who fail to re-register by this new deadline will be struck off from the registry, and will not be able to carry on business [&hellip;]</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="pl-md-4">
<div class="font-weight-bold"><a class="text-vdbpurple" href="https://www.vdb-loi.com/mm_publications/tax-notes-draft-union-tax-law-2018-2019/">Tax Notes: Draft Union Tax Law 2018–2019</a></div>
<div class="text-vdbgray small">September 19, 2018</div>
<div><a class="font-italic text-vdbaqua small" href="https://www.vdb-loi.com/mm_publications/tax-notes-draft-union-tax-law-2018-2019/">https://www.vdb-loi.com/mm_publications/tax-notes-draft-union-tax-law-2018-2019/</a></div>
<div class="font-italic"><p>Due to the change in financial year, the end of the six-month gap period is approaching and the Union Parliament (“Pyidaungsu Hluttaw”) has announced a draft Union Tax Law 2018–2019 (“Draft UTL”) which will be effective from 1 October 2018. A few interesting points from the Draft UTL are outlined below: Financial year end Under [&hellip;]</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="pl-md-4">
<div class="font-weight-bold"><a class="text-vdbpurple" href="https://www.vdb-loi.com/mm_publications/tax-notes-myanmar-union-tax-law-2018-updates/">Tax notes: Myanmar Union Tax Law 2018 updates</a></div>
<div class="text-vdbgray small">March 30, 2018</div>
<div><a class="font-italic text-vdbaqua small" href="https://www.vdb-loi.com/mm_publications/tax-notes-myanmar-union-tax-law-2018-updates/">https://www.vdb-loi.com/mm_publications/tax-notes-myanmar-union-tax-law-2018-updates/</a></div>
<div class="font-italic"><p>The Union Parliament (the Pyidaungsu Hluttaw) enacted the Union Tax Law 2018 (“UTL 2018”) on 30 March 2018, which went into effect on 1 April 2018. Below we provide a synopsis of the points most pertinent for taxpayers this year. The biggest change from the draft UTL 2018 is that the tax amnesty on undisclosed [&hellip;]</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="pl-md-4">
<div class="font-weight-bold"><a class="text-vdbpurple" href="https://www.vdb-loi.com/mm_publications/tax-note-whats-in-store-for-taxpayers-under-the-union-tax-law-2018/">Tax Note: What’s in store for taxpayers under the Union Tax Law 2018?</a></div>
<div class="text-vdbgray small">March 9, 2018</div>
<div><a class="font-italic text-vdbaqua small" href="https://www.vdb-loi.com/mm_publications/tax-note-whats-in-store-for-taxpayers-under-the-union-tax-law-2018/">https://www.vdb-loi.com/mm_publications/tax-note-whats-in-store-for-taxpayers-under-the-union-tax-law-2018/</a></div>
<div class="font-italic"><p>The financial year-end is approaching and the Union Parliament (the Pyidaungsu Hluttaw) finally announced the draft Union Tax Law (“Draft UTL”) 2018 on 13 February 2018, which will go into effect on 1 April 2018. The Draft UTL finally clears up the confusion regarding changes in the financial year. The income year will remain the [&hellip;]</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="pl-md-4">
<div class="font-weight-bold"><a class="text-vdbpurple" href="https://www.vdb-loi.com/mm_publications/myanmars-union-tax-law-2017-changes-for-specific-goods-tax/">Myanmar’s Union Tax Law 2017: Changes for Specific Goods Tax</a></div>
<div class="text-vdbgray small">May 29, 2017</div>
<div><a class="font-italic text-vdbaqua small" href="https://www.vdb-loi.com/mm_publications/myanmars-union-tax-law-2017-changes-for-specific-goods-tax/">https://www.vdb-loi.com/mm_publications/myanmars-union-tax-law-2017-changes-for-specific-goods-tax/</a></div>
<div class="font-italic"><p>A shifting economic and political landscape is driving significant changes in Myanmar’s tax sector. Many amendments have been enacted in this fiscal year, including the changes announced in the Union Tax Law 2017.</p>
</div>
